name: Farid Siddiqui
text:
Nestled near Char Minar Chowrangi, Bahadurabad, this roadside restaurant offers a delightful culinary experience. The service is warm and welcoming, contributing to the overall positive ambiance. However, given its roadside location, don't anticipate a lavish setting.

The pricing falls between moderate and slightly higher, justified by the extensive menu featuring diverse options of daal, chicken, vegetables, and more. The variety compensates for the limited offerings of naan, chapati, and soft drinks, occasionally complemented by a simple salad during daytime hours.

While street parking is available at no cost, securing a spot might pose a challenge due to the presence of beggars. Despite this, the restaurant remains a good choice for those seeking affordable yet varied dishes. The proximity to Smart Cut Hair Saloon adds convenience to the location. Overall, it's a recommended spot for a satisfying meal, especially if you can navigate the quirks of its roadside setting.
title: New Sadabahar Restaurant

address: 318 Tariq Rd، near Liberty Signal، CC Area Block 2 P.E.C.H.S., Karachi, Pakistan
name: Anmol Rajput
text:
Hello, this is Anmol Rajput.

I’m a big fan of the Zinger from Silver Spoon. A couple of months ago, I had a bad experience with their Zinger—it wasn’t cooked properly. I complained and decided not to return, opting instead for KFC, which is good but not my first choice.

Last night, I decided to give Silver Spoon another chance and was thrilled to find that their Zinger Broast was excellent. The seating area had also improved significantly. I even took home two parcels of their Zinger Broast. My favorite dishes—Zinger Broast, Beef Botti, Beef Bihari,Handi Chicken, and Chicken Chowmein—were all fantastic as always.

If you’ve stopped going there, I highly recommend you visit again. The service and food quality are now much better..
Thanks😻
title: Silver Spoon Snacks

name: Nabiha Gul

The flavors were perfectly balanced, and the rolls were made with great care. Highly recommend giving them a try if you’re in the mood for something delicious!
title: Silver Spoon Snacks

address: 318 Tariq Rd، near Liberty Signal، CC Area Block 2 P.E.C.H.S., Karachi, Pakistan
name: Ashar Sherwani
text:
Silver spoon restaurant is said to be the pioneer in introducing  chatni rolls in karachi, their rolls are good, but i personally feel it's overrated. I think many other people are providing much better value and taste like mirchi 360 hot n roll etc. the Club sandwich and Zinger, broast are just average. Service was fast, staff was cooperative.
They are said to be  the one who started the Paratha Roll trend in karachi. And their product is still the best!
The quality and the flavour is still the same after all these years.
And when you are there, don’t forget to try their other BBQ items and chicken karahi.
They have a small AC dinning hall.
title: Silver Spoon Snacks

address: 318 Tariq Rd، near Liberty Signal، CC Area Block 2 P.E.C.H.S., Karachi, Pakistan
name: Imran Noorani
text:
I’ve been going to Silver Spoon on and off for years. Some items are really good, but others can be a hit or miss. Their rolls are still one of the best in town—especially the malai boti roll and beef bihari roll. I also enjoy their chicken handi and chowmein.

A while back, I had a bad experience with their Zinger Broast, so I stopped going. But recently, I went again and was surprised by the improvement. The Zinger was well-cooked, fresh, and tasted great. The seating area also looked better than before, though still quite basic.

However, not everything on the menu is good. I tried their chicken cheeseburger and didn’t like it at all. It was full of ginger and garlic, and the patty felt raw. So I’d avoid their fast food items, except the Zinger Broast which was much better this time.

Overall, I’d rate it 3.5 out of 5. Great for BBQ and rolls, but service and consistency need a bit of work. Worth trying again if you haven’t been there in a while.
title: Silver Spoon Snacks

address: 318 Tariq Rd، near Liberty Signal، CC Area Block 2 P.E.C.H.S., Karachi, Pakistan
name: Badar Siddiqi
text:
I was shopping in the area so decided to grab something quick from this fast food place. I got there quite early for dinner so mostly they were getting their orders ready for delivery. I saw several delivery guys waiting to pickup their orders. I didn't see any menu on the reception so I asked for one and ordered a couple of plates of Chicken Malai Boti. I had to wait about 15 minutes when I was told that my order was ready. I was handed one box in a shopper so I asked them just to confirm if it had two plates inside and I was told it's only a single order. I told them that I had ordered two plates, not one, and showed the receipt as a proof. They talked among themselves and asked me to wait further while they get my second plate ready. The second plate arrived after 10 minutes. I am glad I checked my order right there at the restaurant because I live very far from this place and if I had found out that my order was short , there was no way I'd drive back this far for one plate.
So my advice to all those who are out there at any food place for a take away and waiting for their order, please take a few minutes and double check your order to make sure you're getting exactly what you ordered and paid for.
Their food, however, has always been good to enjoy. They've been in the business for a very long time now and have a very strong base of their loyal customers. They are open from 11 am to midnight everyday.
Updated 2nd May, 2023. Now that I've been going there often, they're looking after me quite well and pay special attention to my special requests. They're always busy serving their loyal guests, both for dine-in and take away. I observe their customers and it's interesting to note that people from all walk of life come here and order all sorts of meals from their extensive menu. They've recently raised their menu prices but it's quite understandable due to current inflation. If you've not been here yet, do visit at least once. Thanks

text: "Yesterday, I visited Silver Spoon on Tariq Road, and it was a delightful experience! I tried the chicken chili with fried rice and also had a chicken tikka roll. The chicken chili was packed with flavor—tender chicken pieces in a deliciously spicy and tangy sauce, perfectly paired with the fried rice, which was light and well-cooked. The chicken tikka roll was equally impressive, with juicy, smoky chicken wrapped in soft, fresh paratha, making it the perfect snack. The portions were generous, and the service was quick and friendly. If you're around Tariq Road and looking for tasty, satisfying food, Silver Spoon is definitely worth a visit!"

name: Engr Dania Hanif
street: Dehli Saudagar Rd No. 4, next to Riaz Masjid
text:
I’ve never actually dined in at this place before, I’ve always opted for takeaway. But this spot seems to be a go-to for the boys on Saturday nights; it’s a favorite among all my guy cousins.

My dad absolutely loves the food here. It’s traditional, Desi, and truly authentic Pakistani-style barbecue, so we ordered it especially for him and as always, he thoroughly enjoyed it! We got their two most popular dishes: the Green Bihari Tikka and Dhaga Kabab, and both lived up to their reputation. The flavors were rich, smoky, and perfectly spiced.

The place isn’t fancy by any means, but it draws a massive crowd. We had to wait nearly 30 minutes to get a table. It was packed; a true testament to how beloved and authentic the food is.
title: Shaikh Abdul Ghaffar Kabab House

address: Dehli Saudagar Rd No. 4, next to Riaz Masjid, Delhi Mercantile Society P.E.C.H.S., Karachi, Pakistan
name: Muhammad Arslan Naveed
street: Dehli Saudagar Rd No. 4, next to Riaz Masjid
text:
I had a great experience at Abdul Ghaffar Kebab House! The place is spacious with multiple floors and plenty of seating, including a separate family area with air conditioning, which was a big plus. The staff is active and helpful.

I tried the fried kebab for the first time in my life—definitely something unique and tasty! I also had malai boti and regular kebabs, and everything was flavorful and well-cooked. The chatni with onions added an extra kick that I really enjoyed.

Overall, a nice place for a casual dine-in with delicious food and good service. Will definitely visit again!
title: Shaikh Abdul Ghaffar Kabab House

text: This iconic Karachi Kebab house serves the best kebabs in Karachi if not in Pakistan. Their specialty is the beef thread kebabs, which have a unique style and taste. This place is so busy that there will always be a wait before getting a seat no matter what time you visit, either indoors, outdoors, or on the roof top. The menu is vast that comprises of a wide variety of amazing Kebabs, along with other grilled meat options in mutton, chicken, and beef, roll paratha, as well as curries and Karhai. For bread options they have the famous Puri Paratha, Naan, as well as Chapati. They also serve desert options including their special small sized Gulab Jaman. The seating comprises of a dining hall in the take away area on ground floor, outdoor seating on the footpath with tables and chairs for four people each, while a much fancier and more private area is on the walk-up roof top first floor which is for families only. Highly recommended restaurant for any one with an ever so slight liking of Kebabs.
title: Shaikh Abdul Ghaffar Kabab House

address: Dehli Saudagar Rd No. 4, next to Riaz Masjid, Delhi Mercantile Society P.E.C.H.S., Karachi, Pakistan

text:
If you’re a true BBQ lover, Abdul Ghaffar Kebab House is a hidden gem that deserves all the hype! Known for its authentic flavors and perfectly grilled meats, this place takes kebabs to the next level. From the moment you step in, the aroma of sizzling kebabs on charcoal grills pulls you in, promising an unforgettable food experience.

The Food – A Meat Lover’s Paradise

⭐ Malai Boti – Incredibly soft and creamy, this dish melts in your mouth with every bite. The balanced spices and rich marinade make it an instant favorite.

⭐ Behari Kebab – Smoky, tender, and packed with bold flavors, these kebabs are marinated to perfection. The spice level is just right, making each bite an explosion of taste.

⭐ Reshmi Kebab – Smooth, delicate, and juicy, Reshmi Kebab is a must-try for those who enjoy subtle flavors with a buttery texture.

⭐ Mutton Kebab – The perfect blend of spices and high-quality mutton makes these kebabs an absolute delight. Juicy, flavorful, and grilled to perfection!

⭐ Kebab Fry – A unique twist on traditional kebabs! Fried to create a crispy exterior while keeping the inside tender and flavorful. Highly recommended for those looking for something different.

Overall Experience

✅ Authentic BBQ flavors with high-quality ingredients.
✅ Perfectly grilled, juicy kebabs that keep you coming back.
✅ Affordable prices considering the top-notch taste and portion sizes.
✅ Fast service despite the high demand.

If you’re craving authentic BBQ with rich, smoky flavors, Abdul Ghaffar Kebab House is the place to be! Rating: 5/5 – A must-visit for all kebab lovers!
title: Shaikh Abdul Ghaffar Kabab House

text:
Shaikh Abdul Ghaffar Kabab House has long been a beloved destination for those seeking authentic Pakistani barbecue. While their food quality and taste remain top-notch, there's certainly room for improvement in terms of service and dining experience for those who are not coming with family.
Their kababs, particularly the dhaga and gola varieties, are a delight to the taste buds, cooked to perfection and bursting with flavor. While the Kabab Fry remains a standout dish. The succulent meat and aromatic spices create a truly memorable culinary experience. The Nihari falls short in term of both taste and meat quantity. It's a shame, as the potential for a truly exceptional Nihari is there, given the restaurant's expertise in other dishes. However, the dining experience could be enhanced with improved service and more comfortable seating arrangements.
While the staff may be friendly, there's often a noticeable delay in service, which can sometimes lead to frustration. Additionally, the seating area could benefit from a renovation to provide a more comfortable and inviting atmosphere for diners.
Overall, Shaikh Abdul Ghaffar Kabab House remains a popular choice for those seeking delicious Pakistani barbecue. By addressing the service and seating issues, they could elevate their dining experience to even greater heights.

text:
Shaikh Abdul Ghaffar Kabab House offers a decent dining experience for both family and friends. The food quality is commendable, and the service is generally good, though the persistent issue of prolonged waiting times may impact the overall experience.

The establishment provides various seating options, including family halls, a rooftop area, indoor halls, and outdoor street seating. However, accessibility can be challenging for older individuals, especially to the upstairs family hall.

While the rooftop lacks a scenic view, it could be suitable for private gatherings during summer. The indoor halls, unfortunately, tend to be overcrowded, limiting the enjoyment of meals.

The outdoor street seating has seen improvements, with a reduction in street beggars, but challenges persist due to randomly parked bikes and blocked streets caused by dropping-off vehicles. This may disrupt the dining experience with constant traffic noise.

Parking poses a significant issue, given the lack of proper designated areas in the residential society, causing inconvenience for both residents and customers. However, the outdoor street sitting area is relatively secure with proper lighting, barriers and security guards.

On a positive note, the vicinity offers convenience with nearby grocery stores, a bakery, and a chai dhaba for post-dinner tea. Additionally, there's a Mosque for those wishing to offer prayers.

In conclusion, Shaikh Abdul Ghaffar Kabab House provides a satisfactory dining option despite its drawbacks and recent price increase too. The environment may not be serene, but the opportunity for prayer and convenient shopping afterward adds to the overall experience.
title: Shaikh Abdul Ghaffar Kabab House

text:
My culinary adventure led me to Shaikh Abdul Ghaffar Kebab House in Karachi, and oh, what a delightful experience it was! Let’s dive into the flavours:
1.	Nihari Nirvana: The Nihari here deserves a standing ovation. Rich, aromatic, and slow-cooked to perfection, it transported me to the heart of Old Karachi. The tender meat, soaked in spices, left me craving for more.
2.	Kebabs with Character: The kebabs—oh, those juicy, smoky kebabs! Whether it’s the kabab fry, chicken tikka, or the Reshmi kabab, each bite is a celebration of flavour. The grill masters at Shaikh Abdul Ghaffar know their craft well.
3.	Ambiance: The restaurant exudes warmth and authenticity. The hustle-bustle, the sizzle of skewers, and the tantalizing aroma—it’s a sensory feast.
4.	Chicken Malai Boti : The chicken won my heart. Moist, flavourful, and with just the right kick, it’s a dish I won’t forget anytime soon.
5.	Aftermath: As I savoured the last spoonful of Nihari, I knew I’d be back. And yes, I did—multiple times!
In summary, Shaikh Abdul Ghaffar Kebab House isn’t just a restaurant; it’s a flavour pilgrimage. If you’re in Karachi, make this your foodie destination. 🌟🍽️
title: Shaikh Abdul Ghaffar Kabab House

address: Dehli Saudagar Rd No. 4, next to Riaz Masjid, Delhi Mercantile Society P.E.C.H.S., Karachi, Pakistan
name: Arun Kumar
street: Dehli Saudagar Rd No. 4, next to Riaz Masjid
text:
My friends and I recently dined at Ghaffar Kabab House, and I must say it was an unforgettable experience. From the moment I stepped in, I was greeted with warm hospitality and a cozy atmosphere. However, it was the exquisite flavors that stole the show and left me wanting more.

We started our culinary journey with the Chicken Malai Boti, and it was a true delight. The succulent pieces of chicken were marinated to perfection, tender and juicy with a creamy texture that melted in my mouth. The blend of spices was balanced just right, making it a heavenly dish that I couldn't get enough of.

Next up, we tried the Bihari Tikka, and it was a revelation. The tender, marinated pieces of beef were cooked to perfection, boasting an irresistible smoky flavor. Each bite was packed with rich spices that complemented the meat beautifully. It was truly a taste sensation.

The Chicken Reshmi Kababs were another highlight of our meal. These kababs were incredibly flavorful, with a delicate blend of spices that enhanced the taste of the tender chicken. The texture was perfect, and the aroma was simply irresistible.

To accompany our delicious kababs, we ordered both naan and paratha. The naan was soft, fluffy, and had a slight crispness on the outside. It was the perfect vehicle for savoring the flavors of the kababs. The paratha, on the other hand, was flaky, buttery, and utterly delicious. It added a touch of indulgence to our meal.

In conclusion, Ghaffar Kabab House is a gem for all food lovers in Karachi. The quality of the food is exceptional, and the flavors are a true testament to the culinary expertise of the chefs. The service was impeccable, and the staff made sure we felt welcome throughout our dining experience. If you're looking for an unforgettable meal filled with delectable kababs and mouthwatering flavors, Ghaffar Kabab House is the place to be. I can't wait to visit again and explore more of their tantalizing menu!
title: Shaikh Abdul Ghaffar Kabab House

One of the best kebab house in the city.

The mutton kebab was very rich, and had a nice taste to it. Malai boti and behari tikka was cooked perfectly. The chatkhara boti was good but its taste was overpowered by the cream on it.
We sat on the top floor, service was good and our order was served quite quickly.
Would recommend.

Fresco Sweets is a true gem for anyone who loves traditional Pakistani sweets with unmatched taste and quality. Their mithai is always fresh, perfectly balanced in sweetness, and beautifully presented — ideal for family gatherings, celebrations, or gifting.

From their classic gulab jamuns and barfi to the delicious samosas and nimco, everything tastes homemade with a premium touch. The staff is courteous, the service is quick, and the cleanliness of the outlet adds to the overall experience.

Whether you're picking up something for a special occasion or just craving a sweet treat, Fresco never disappoints. Highly recommended for all sweet lovers!

text:
I was visiting this place on recommendations of someone for Dahi Bhallay. Being from Punjab my idea of Dahi Bhallay was quite different, mine included chopped onions, green chilli, tomatoes and spices (so it was overall a spicy dish with a hint of Chana Chaat). But I was in for a surprise as I saw chickpea flour dough balls floating in sweet yogurt. They looked quite bland, but the person added some Paapdi and spices over it turning it into an amazing blend of sweet and spicy yogurt with those soft dough balls. It was a great experience and I’d definitely recommend it.
Although I was tempted to try their Arabic Paratha as well, but my caloric intake was done for the day. So, left Paratha for another trip to the amazing and historic Burns Road.

text:
After lot of hype decided to try the Saudi chicken sandwich. Rs. 570/_. Have to admit it's really filling and good 👌🏻😌
However in the ending it can get a bit dry. Due to lack of sauce.
The sandwich is more like a pita bread with a juicy patty, sauce , fries and pickles.  Non spicy

Alongside also ordered the large cheddar fries for Rs. 500/- . Disappointed due to inflation the cup isn't really a large size and the cheddar cheese was just on top so the fries that are below are basically plain.

address: MBL Panorama Karachi Cantonment, Karachi, Pakistan
name: ikram khan
text:
"I recently visited OPTP Atrium that had a diverse menu featuring a variety of options such as burgers, chicken wings, nuggets, pizza, fries, and different meal combinations. Overall, I was impressed with the quality of the food and the range of options available.

One of the standout items on the menu were the burgers. They had a variety of different types of burgers, from classic cheeseburgers to more unique options like a BBQ bacon burger or a veggie burger. The burgers were cooked to perfection and were served on fresh buns with all the fixings. The patties were juicy and flavorful, and the toppings were fresh and delicious.

The chicken wings were also a hit. They had a few different sauce options, and I opted for the spicy buffalo sauce. The wings were crispy on the outside and juicy on the inside, and the sauce had the perfect level of heat. I also tried the nuggets, which were equally delicious. They were crispy and tender, and the breading was seasoned just right.

In addition to the burgers, wings, and nuggets, they also had pizza on the menu. I was a bit hesitant to try it at a fast food restaurant, but I was pleasantly surprised. The pizza was hot and fresh, with a crispy crust and plenty of toppings. It was definitely a solid option if you're in the mood for something different.

Of course, no fast food meal is complete without fries, and this restaurant did not disappoint in that department. The fries were hot and crispy, with the perfect amount of salt. They also had a few different dipping sauces available, which was a nice touch.

One thing I appreciated about this restaurant was the variety of meal options available. They had a few different combos that included a burger or sandwich, fries, and a drink. They also had a few different "box" options, which included a mix of different items like nuggets, wings, fries, and a drink. This made it easy to order for a group or to try a few different things at once.

Overall, I was very impressed with this fast food restaurant. The Prices were a bit above average but the food was rich in taste, the menu had a lot of variety, and the meal options made it easy to customize your order. If you're in the mood for a quick and tasty meal, this place is definitely worth a visit."

text: They have fresly prepared nimko and have fried appetizers like samosas etc... Now what they are truly known for is their bhelpuri mix chat, very refreshing, sweet, savory, and very light snack for on the go. A flavor bomb that is budget friendly and will keep you craving for more.
title: Ezzy Nimco

address: Dr Daud Pota Rd, Saddar Karachi, 74400, Pakistan
name: Naseer
responseFromOwnerText: Thank you Sir we Ezzy Nimco really appreciate your feed back
text:
There are multiple shops of Nimko in the Sadar Empress market, however Ezzy Nimco is on the top of the line with different verities. You can choose either already mixed Nimko or you can build you own by choose what you need in the mix nimko, this option is available in the Galee (extension of Ezzy Nimko shop) just besides the main shop.

Parking:
There is no as such parking available so better either come with someone who can sit in the car during your purchase. Or Park the car besides the Rambo Center where there is a charged parking (not sure if it is still available there).
title: Ezzy Nimco

address: Dr Daud Pota Rd, Saddar Saddar Town, Karachi, Pakistan
name: Zubair Mughis
responseFromOwnerText: Thank you so much for your positive rating! We're thrilled to hear that you had a great experience with us. We're committed to providing excellent service, and it's always rewarding to receive such positive feedback. We look forward to serving you again in the future!
text:
Tried their famous Chicken Biryani and newly introduced beef Pulao today

Taste wise beef pulao is okay and price is also economical but there are other better options available in the vicinity

Chicken Biryani is good with perfectly cooked rice and adequate masala though i found it to be a bit spicy (wife said its not 😁)

Overall recommended for a quick snacking but parking is a grave issue here (we ate it while sitting inside our car)

A try is a must 👍

P.S: beef biryani is also available

Price list:

150Rs for 250gms Chicken Biryani
160Rs for 250gms beef pulao 👍
title: Laziz Biryani and Pulao

name: Ahsan Ahmed
street: V2FJ+V64, Shop # 02 Saghar Manzil Bahaduryar Jung Road, Clayton Rd
text:
Dixy Pizza, located in Karachi, is known for its warm and inviting atmosphere, offering a variety of pizzas that have garnered positive feedback from patrons. Customers appreciate the generous toppings and flavorful combinations, making it a popular choice for pizza enthusiasts in the area.

The staff at Dixy Pizza are often described as friendly and helpful, contributing to a pleasant dining experience. However, during peak hours, the restaurant can become quite busy, which may lead to longer waiting times. Despite this, many find that the quality of the food and reasonable prices make it worth the wait.

In addition to pizzas, Dixy offers a range of other items, including chicken burgers and wings, which have also received favorable reviews. The establishment maintains a clean environment, and the food is typically served fresh and hot.

Overall, Dixy Pizza is considered a solid option for those seeking a satisfying meal in Karachi, with its diverse menu and welcoming ambiance contributing to its reputation as a go-to spot for both locals and visitors.
title: Dixy Pizza

name: Md Arif Kasim (Arif Fiego)
text:
Had a lovely dinner at Kolachi Pakistan with my friends. The view was absolutely stunning — we got to enjoy the sea breeze and watch the sunset right from our table. We stayed from evening till night and really enjoyed the atmosphere. The steak was delicious, and the service was friendly and attentive.

However, just a heads up — there was a hidden service charge of 3,000 rupees, which we only found out about when the bill arrived. It would’ve been better if this was mentioned earlier. Still, overall it was a memorable dining experience!
title: Kolachi Restaurant

address: Ocean Towers، 5Th, Khayaban-e-Iqbal, Block 9 Clifton, Karachi, 75600, Pakistan
name: Ariba Azhar
text: Okay so Kolachi took over this restaurant “Taj Darbar” at highway. It was a pretty avg experience here. The service was definitely good but there’s room for improvement. The food was good, not the best. The vibes were the same as taj darbar and I’ve been there many times so it wasn’t giving. The portion sizes were a bit off too. The lahori fish was tasteless and then they compensated it with dynamite prawns, which were good.
title: Kolachi Restaurant

address: Ocean Towers، 5Th, Khayaban-e-Iqbal, Block 9 Clifton, Karachi, 75600, Pakistan
name: Muhammad Moudood
text: The restaurant is an amazing place for the beautiful seaside view and overall aesthetic. The food was decent and service was excellent. The best time to go is around sunset hours and you should be ready to expect a queue before receiving a table unless you reserve it before hand.

address: Ocean Towers، 5Th, Khayaban-e-Iqbal, Block 9 Clifton, Karachi, 75600, Pakistan
name: rao umair afzaal
text:
4.5 stars for the place !

A mandatory visit to this place as it was my first visit to karachi.

The service right from the start was great and continued till the moment we left the place. Its amazing to see them cater to such a huge crowd and still make them feel great!

As per food,  our local friend suggested :
Hunzai Mutton Kebab - decent!
Mutton karhai was good too, everyone seemed to love it, for me it was more of black pepper taste thus half the less star, and similar with another karhai we had- paneeri karhai .

title: Kolachi Restaurant

address: Ocean Towers، 5Th, Khayaban-e-Iqbal, Block 9 Clifton, Karachi, 75600, Pakistan
name: Asif Iqbal
text:
Kolachi—a stunning restaurant in Karachi, perfectly situated along the beach.

We were initially referred to Do Darya, but somehow ended up at Kolachi, and we never regretted it. When I mentioned to one of the managers that we were visiting from Lahore, they graciously offered us the dreamiest seats—right at the corner of the restaurant, where the panoramic sea view was simply breathtaking.

The sight of birds soaring over the ocean, resembling pearls scattered across the waves, added to the enchanting atmosphere.

As for the food, Karachiites never disappoint when it comes to flavor. We indulged in their fish pakoras and other local specialties, and the experience was nothing short of amazing.
title: Kolachi Restaurant

name: Irfan Rauf
text: I recently dined at Kolachi Restaurant, inside Ocean Mall, and it was an outstanding experience. The food was excellent, with each dish perfectly crafted and bursting with flavor. The service was top-notch, with attentive and friendly staff who made us feel welcome throughout our meal. But what truly set this place apart was the ambiance—absolutely on top. The atmosphere was inviting and beautifully designed, creating the perfect setting for an unforgettable dining experience. I highly recommend Kolachi to anyone looking for a fantastic meal in an exceptional setting!

name: Farid Baber
text: With auspicious looks and beautiful environment this restaurant serves so delicious Pakistani and Continental dishes with fresh ingredients. We have been served with fresh breezy mint margaritas, Dhaka fish, dynamite Prawn,chicken karahi afghani pulao, Manchurian,garlic naan, salad and raita. The dessert suji halwa was so yummy. Very efficient and quick service by staff specially waiter Hakeem’s dedication to serving was excellent. Fully recommended for family and friends.
title: Kolachi Restaurant

text: One of the most ethereal dining experiences I’ve had. We went after a rainy day for dinner, and had a view that overlooked a misty sea speckled with flocks of white birds. If the authentic, delicious food weren’t as mesmerising as the ambience, we probably would have forgotten we were there for dinner.
title: Kolachi Restaurant

name: Shehryar Anees
text:
Kolachi is one of the best dining experiences in Karachi. As the restaurant is situated at the top of Ocean Mall, the restaurant offers an extensive view of the city with a beautiful atmosphere, offering quite a pleasant dining experience after shopping or casual visits.

Indoor and outdoor, both options are available, offering an excellent ambience. Staff is very cooperative, and serving time is quite reasonable.

name: Bushra Khan
text:
I’ve been eating at Kolachis for over 10 years now. It’s been a while since I went to the restaurant since we just order in.
But nothing has changed, the food is STILL excellent, the service even better. They always call you the next day after  delivery order to check if everything was okay, if not they want to make it up to you. If a dish is not up to your liking at the restaurant they take it away and remove it from the bill. They could teach a thing or 2 to the general public about service!!!

Their reshmi kebabs are heaven on a plate, and the malai boti never fails to be tender. I tried their Peshawari chicken karai last night and what a treat that was.

Highly recommended- won’t disappoint and keep you coming back for more!
title: Kolachi Restaurant

address: Ocean Towers، 5Th, Khayaban-e-Iqbal, Block 9 Clifton, Karachi, 75600, Pakistan
name: Abdul Sami
text:
Went to this restaurant for dinner on November 26, 2023 as group of 7.

Place looks stunning and very picturesque located at seaside.

This is huge restaurant which was very busy too.

Unfortunately good things ends as soon the food arrives. We ordered many items and non was tasty. Most of the items were very salty and in small portions.

Chicken Tikka was came in foil which make it soggy, also size of tikka was like for kids meal.

They charge top price for every items. If food is good then we don’t mind hung price but it was terrible.

After the meal they bring the phone to us to record the review. I didn’t give good review there as well. They quick bring two pieces of very small Malahi tikka ( just two pieces) for me to try as compensation.this was embarrassing that after spending $23,000 rupees this is what we got ( two pieces) we were not looking for any compensation anyway but felt embarrassed.

Lightning was also strange as everything is red in color and you don’t even see true color of food you order.

This restaurant is great to take pictures of your Social Media page not for eating here.

Stay away there much better options are available.

American Steak Sandwich
امریکن اسٹیک سینڈوچ آرڈر کیا تھا مجھے امید تھی کہ سینڈوچ میں مصالحے دار گوشت کا کوئی بڑا سا ٹکڑا ہوگا مگر اس میں قیمہ تھا، مصالحے کم تھے مرچ بھی کم تھی نفاست سے اسمبل کیا گیا تھا کھانے میں آسان تھا سینڈوچ فلنگ مناسب تھی اس لئے کھاتے وقت سینڈوچ سے باہر نہیں گری کیچپ کی کوالٹی بھی مناسب تھی۔ شاید یہ امریکیوں کا ذوق ایسا ہی ہوگا جو مجھے تو سمجھ نہیں آیا امریکیوں کو برا لگتا تو لگے بھئی صاف بات ہے۔
textTranslated:
American Steak Sandwich
Ordered the American Steak Sandwich I was expecting a big piece of spicy meat in the sandwich but it was minced, the spices were lacking, the chili was also lacking, it was delicately assembled, it was easy to eat, the sandwich filling was just right. The quality of the ketchup was also decent as it did not fall out of the sandwich while eating. Maybe it will be the taste of Americans which I don't understand. It is clear if Americans feel bad.

text: Kolachi is an exquisite dining establishment with stunning ambiance. address: Ocean Towers، 5Th, Khayaban-e-Iqbal, Block 9 Clifton, Karachi, 75600, Pakistan
name: Alishah Jamal (AJ)
text: 4.5/5 very good and quality restaurant. We got the dynamite chicken, adana kebab, chicken hundi, garlic naan, and one other type of naan. All the dishes were excellent and the quality of the ingredients were impressive. The kebab was good and tasted similar to adana kebab you would find in turkish restaurants; not the same but similar. Quality of the meat was good too. The chicken hundi was also quality, but small portions for the amount you pay. The dynamite chicken was excellent and the meat was tender and soft. Overall great restaurant that is overpriced, but quality food. Would recommend!
title: Kolachi Restaurant

address: Muhammad Bin Qasim Rd, Saddar Burns Road, Karachi, 75500, Pakistan
name: achakzai Ahmed
text:
*★★★★☆ Amazing Food, Cozy Space - A Little Investment Would Make It Perfect!**
> The food is FANTASTIC! Especially the Shapator roll - incredible flavor (though the paratha was a bit thinner than a normal roll). But the real star is the taste - some of the best around.
>
> **Small request for the owner:** The dining area gets quite warm and congested with only 2 fans. It would be wonderful if you could **invest in expanding or better ventilating the space** - maybe more fans, AC, or a larger area? Not a complaint, just friendly guidance! More comfort = more customers enjoying your delicious food longer.
>
> Still highly recommended for the incredible flavors! 🙏
title: Spicy Khan Restaurant

address: Muhammad Bin Qasim Rd, Saddar Burns Road, Karachi, 75500, Pakistan
name: Bisma Haya
text:
Their Shaparter Roll is absolutely fantastic—packed with rich flavors and a perfect balance of spices. The Arabic Shawarma is another highlight.Their sandwiches are well-prepared and satisfying.

However, while the food is top-notch, the management and service need serious improvement. We had to wait for around 45 minutes, and despite taking our order multiple times (almost 2-3 times), they failed to deliver it. This lack of coordination made the experience frustrating.
title: Spicy Khan Restaurant
